<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>In Haml:<p><pre><code>  .span3
    = render :partial =&#62; "col1"
  .span3
    = render :partial =&#62; "col2"
  .span3
    = render :partial =&#62; "col3"
  .span3
    = render :partial =&#62; "col4"
</code></pre>
Or, to do 3-col:<p><pre><code>  .span4
    = render :partial =&#62; "col1"
  .span4
    = render :partial =&#62; "col2"
  .span4
    = render :partial =&#62; "col3"
</code></pre>
Nothing in the partial needs to especially care about the grid (as long as its simple) --- but if it wanted to, it could nest columns.</font></span><p><font size=1><u><a href="reply?id=3507402&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%61%35%6e%36%67%31%68%45%5a%48">reply</a></u></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=320></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3507732 href="vote?for=3507732&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%61%35%6e%36%67%31%68%45%5a%48"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3507732></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=aaronbrethorst">aaronbrethorst</a> 10 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3507732">link</a></span></div><br>
<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>or better yet, you have semantically named elements and assign them column values in your .less file:<p><pre><code>    #sidebar {
      .makeColumn(4);
    }
    #main_pane {
      .makeColumn(8);
    }

    #sidebar
      = render :partial =&#62; 'common/sidebar'
    #main_pane
      = yield</code></pre></font></span><p><font size=1><u><a href="reply?id=3507732&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%61%35%6e%36%67%31%68%45%5a%48">reply</a></u></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=280></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3507417 href="vote?for=3507417&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%61%35%6e%36%67%31%68%45%5a%48"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3507417></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=dangrossman">dangrossman</a> 11 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3507417">link</a></span></div><br>
<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>You don't have to edit the CSS at all. You don't even have to open the file, ever, to use Bootstrap. Just link it in the head of your document like any stylesheet and use the class names from the documentation.<p>Want something on your page to be 3 columns wide? &#60;div class="span3"&#62;...&#60;/div&#62;<p>Want to make it 4 columns wide instead? &#60;div class="span4"&#62;...&#60;/div&#62;</font></span><p><font size=1><u><a href="reply?id=3507417&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%61%35%6e%36%67%31%68%45%5a%48">reply</a></u></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=320></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3507516 href="vote?for=3507516&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%61%35%6e%36%67%31%68%45%5a%48"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3507516></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=tstegart">tstegart</a> 11 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3507516">link</a></span></div><br>
